  "description": "Olof August Bergholtz was a Swedish Mayor born on December 13, 1904 in Västervik, Sweden. He was married to Karin Bengtsson in 1934 and had two children, Inga and Gunnar. Bergholtz graduated with a law degree in 1927 and went on to serve as various legal positions including Acting Assistant Prosecutor, Assessor, Advocate Prosecutor, Secretary of Revenue, and Court Adviser. Bergholtz was appointed as Mayor of Växjö in 1946 and was a member of various organizations including the Kronoberg County Maternity Help Association, 1st Kronoberg County Savings Bank, and the Finance Committee in Växjö. He wrote a book entitled 'Child support and maintenance advance payments'. Bergholtz received the Royal Order of the North Star." 
